text: Alfred Ebanks (born 1 September 1953) is a Caymanian former cyclist. He competed at the 1984 Summer Olympics, 1988 Summer Olympics and the 1992 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1953 births Category:Living people Category:Caymanian male cyclists Category:Olympic cyclists of the Cayman Islands Category:Cyclists at the 1984 Summer Olympics Category:Cyclists at the 1988 Summer Olympics Category:Cyclists at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
